Ask HN: Why aren't there any tools that detect memory leaks in JavaScript (web)?
text: Why is it that Javascript (in the browser) doesn't have any tools that would allow developers to perform memory leaks detection? Chrome has a heap profiler that can take memory snapshots, but it feels nothing like tools like Valgrind.
